  "prompt": "Where can I get my short story reviewed?",
  "response": "There are several places where you can get your short story reviewed:\n\n1. **Writing Communities and Forums**:\n   - **Absolute Write Water Cooler**: Large community where you can share your work and receive critiques.\n   - **Scribophile**: A writing group where members critique each others' work.\n   - **Critique Circle**: Another peer-review community for writers.\n\n2. **Social Media and Online Platforms**:\n   - **Reddit**: Subreddits like r/writing, r/writerchat, and r/DestructiveReaders offer community critique and feedback.\n   - **Twitter**: You can connect with writers and reviewers using hashtags like #amwriting and #writerscommunity.\n\n3. **Writing Groups and Workshops**:\n   - Local writing groups often provide workshops and critique sessions.\n   - Online workshops and writing courses frequently offer peer review opportunities.\n\n4. **Professional Editors**:\n   - You can hire a professional editor for a more polished critique through websites like Reedsy or Upwork.\n\n5. **Beta Readers**:\n   - Websites like BetaBooks or Goodreads have programs to connect writers with beta readers who provide feedback.\n\nChoose the option that best aligns with your goals\u2014whether you're looking for quick, informal feedback or professional critique.",
